This paper discusses the challenges of training large deep convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GPUs and distributed training, which are common topics in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of software tools and packages, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
